## Introduction  {#introduction}

1. Consultants are informed via email that they can start submitting Timesheets during the assigned Project or after Project was finished

2. Important elements for the process:  
   1. Consultant’s email inbox  
   2. Consultant’s My Projects webpage

## 1st step \- Consultant receives email to access Timesheets {#1st-step---consultant-receives-email-to-access-timesheets}

1. Process starts with an email received by Consultant   
   1. Email is sent by automation from H\&J Petro after project was setup in HubSpot  
   2. Consultant receives an email into his inbox (email is previously set in HubSpot)  
      ![][image1]  
2. Consultant should click on the link **ACCESS YOUR TIMESHEETS** from the email

## 2nd step \- Consultant opens My Project webpage  {#2nd-step---consultant-opens-my-project-webpage}

1. Click on the link from received email, which will take Consultant to My Project webpage  
   1. **Important note**: *Consultant will always use the same link for inserting timesheets. Therefore, it is helpful for the consultant to bookmark this link in the browser*  
      

2. Input password, currently consultant123 (6/3/2024)  
3. All active Consultant projects will be listed

### My project web page elements {#my-project-web-page-elements}

1. **Project**: the name of the project Consultant is hired for  
2. **Customer**: the name of the client Consultant is hired for  
3. **Operator**: the name of the Operator (can be the same or different then Customer)  
4. **EXISTING LINE ITEMS** button \- click on it to see timesheet line items created by Today  
5. **NEW LINE ITEMS** button \- click on it to create new timesheet line item   
6. It’s clearly communicated if the Project is locked and therefore Timesheets line items can’t be added   
   1. There is a notice: The Project is locked  
   2. **NEW LINE ITEM** button is unavailable  
   3. **Important note**: *Project is locked if it is completed* 

## 3rd step \- Consultant creates Timesheet line items {#3rd-step---consultant-creates-timesheet-line-items}

1. Consultant shall identify **Project** to create timesheet line item from the list  
2. Next \- click on **NEW LINE ITEM** button  
     
     
     
     
     
     
     
3. On the next page consultant will be informed of existing line items and prompted to create new one  
     
     
     
     
     
     
     
     
     
     
4. Click on the **INSERT NEW LINE ITEM** button

   

### Fill Out The Timesheet {#fill-out-the-timesheet}

1. **Step 1** \- Consultant shall **Select Role** he is hired for on the Project \- available values will be listed in a drop down \- and click on **NEXT STEP** button  
   

2. **Step 2** \- Consultant shall **Select Job/Service** for which he is about to create the timesheet line item \- available values will be listed in a drop down and click on **NEXT STEP** button  
     
     
     
     
     
     
     
     
     
     
     
     
     
     
     
     
     
     
     
3. **Step 3** \- Consultant shall **Select Input Type** \- which can be **date range** or **Initial date/Time**  
   ![][image2]  
     
     
     
     
     
     
     
     
     
     
4. **If selected input type is date range**   
   1. Click on **Select Date Range** to update date using calendar  
   2. Click on **Select Start/End Time** to update start/end working time for the selected date range  
   3. Click on **Select Well** and select the well from the dropdown list

   4. Click on **Select Unit** and select **Hourly** or **Daily** rates for selected date range   
      1. If **Day** is selected as Unit, **Select Quantity** will become available and the Consultant could update part of the day he was working for (whole day, half a day, 0.7 days etc..)  
      2. If **Hour** is selected as Unit, **Select Quantity** will be unavailable  
5. After Input Type, Date range, Start/End Time, Well, Unit and Quantity are selected, consultant shall click on **INSERT LINE ITEMS NOW** button

![][image3]

6. On the next screen line item range is created based on the selected data on the previous screen and Consultant can edit each of the lines  
   

7. On the same page Consultant can add information for a different well by selecting the data and clicking on the **INSERT LINE ITEM** button  
   ![][image4]  
     
   1. **Important note**: *If Consultant select Custom value for Wells/Units, process will be similar to explained above starting from bullet 4, except \- missing information will have to be updated manually*  
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
8. Once all Timesheets line items are updated, Consultant shall click on **CONFIRM** button  
9. The final step is to **SUBMIT** the timesheet line item by clicking on the button with the same name

   1. **Important note**: Please, be patient for a couple of seconds. The screen will look like this:  
      

### Successfully Inserted Timesheet info {#successfully-inserted-timesheet-info}

1. After all steps are done based on the above instructions, the Consultant will be informed that Timesheet line items were successfully   
   ![][image5]  
2. Optionally, click on the **ALL TIMESHEETS FOR THIS PROJECT** button, which will list all timesheet line items created by the Consultant for the project  
     
 


   

3. At this point Consultant can double check entry and decide to  
   1. **UPDATE LINE ITEM** \- click corresponding button  
   2. **DELETE LINE ITEM** \- click corresponding button

         
4. After finishing updates of existing line items, Consultant can  
   1. **INSERT ANOTHER LINE ITEM** \- click corresponding button \- and then Consultant shall repeat steps from [**Fill Out The Timesheet \- Step 1**](#bookmark=id.ckb1v0qmm1uj)  
   2. **SUBMIT A REQUEST FOR APPROVAL** \- click corresponding button  
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
      

## 4th step \- Submitting a request for approval {#4th-step---submitting-a-request-for-approval}

1. Consultant shall click on the **SUBMIT A REQUEST FOR APPROVAL** button after all line items were submitted  
2. Approver will receive Consultant request  
3. Consultant will be notified via email with approval status
